org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.impl

Class GridDialectLogger

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.impl.ForwardingGridDialect<Serializable>
      • org.hibernate.ogm.dialect.impl.GridDialectLogger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, BatchableGridDialect, IdentityColumnAwareGridDialect, OptimisticLockingAwareGridDialect, QueryableGridDialect<Serializable>, GridDialect, SessionFactoryLifecycleAwareDialect, Service, Configurable, ServiceRegistryAwareService

    public class GridDialectLogger
extends ForwardingGridDialect<Serializable>
    A wrapper dialect that logs any performance-relevant calls performed on the real dialect. It is only used when this class's logger level is set to Trace
    Author:
    Sebastien Lorber (lorber.sebastien@gmail.com), Emmanuel Bernard <emmanuel@hibernate.org>
    See Also:
    GridDialectInitiator, Serialized Form

      • createTuple

        public Tuple createTuple(EntityKey key,
                TupleContext tupleContext)
        Description copied from interface: GridDialect
        Creates a new tuple for the given entity key.

        Only invoked if no tuple is present yet for the given key. Implementations should not perform a round-trip to the datastore but rather return a transient instance. The OGM engine will invoke GridDialect.insertOrUpdateTuple(EntityKey, Tuple, TupleContext) subsequently.

        Columns in the tuple may represent properties of the corresponding entity as well as *-to-one associations to other entities. Implementations may choose to persist the latter e.g. in form of fields or as actual links/relationships to the element representing the associated entity. In case of multi-column keys, the corresponding association role for a given column can be obtained from the passed tuple context.

        Specified by:
        createTuple in interface GridDialect
        Overrides:
        createTuple in class ForwardingGridDialect<Serializable>
        Parameters:
        key - The tuple identifier
        tupleContext - Contains additional information that might be used to create the tuple
        Returns:
        the created tuple

      • createAssociation

        public Association createAssociation(AssociationKey key,
                            AssociationContext associationContext)
        Description copied from interface: GridDialect
        Creates a new (empty) association for storing the tuples representing the rows corresponding to the given key.

        Only invoked if the association does not yet exist in the datastore. Implementations should not perform a round-trip to the datastore but rather return a transient instance. The OGM engine will invoke GridDialect.insertOrUpdateAssociation(AssociationKey, Association, AssociationContext) subsequently.

        Description copied from interface: GridDialect
